parameters:
\N<Boss-kun>Oh? What is it, Boku-chan? Do you want to go
ahead...? I bet you want to do some 'grass sliding,' don't
you?

\N<Boss-kun>What, you don't know? Alright, I'll tell you,
so go get a cardboard box.

\N<Boss-kun>If you go to the Aoki Store in the shopping
district, they'll give it to you. Usually there's an old man
at the store, but during summer vacation, a somewhat
intimidating onee-chan is taking care of the shop.
\N<Boku>I see... Should I go check it out?

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, Boku-chan. Did you bring the cardboard box?
In that case, let's have a race on the grass slope. If you
can beat me, I'll show you a secret fishing spot.

\N<Boss-kun>Oh? Another race on the grass slope? Alright,
let's do it!
Let's do it! Let's do it!

\N<Boss-kun>Impressive courage! In that case, let's go to
the top of the ski resort.

\N<Boss-kun>Listen up. The rules are simple. We'll slide
down from here to the bottom and the one who passes through
the most checkpoints wins. The checkpoints will be shining
brightly to make them noticeable.
\N<Boku>Checkpoints? So it's not just about being fast?

\N<Boss-kun>There was a rule change a few years ago because
it was deemed dangerous to compete solely based on speed.

\N<Boss-kun>Here's some advice for the end. Be careful
because you'll bounce if you step on a step. Alright then,
are you ready? Enough with the chit-chat, let's begin!

\N<Boss-kun>What's wrong, did you get scared? Come at me
anytime.
\N<Boku>Yay! I won! So, where's the best fishing spot?

\N<Boss-kun>Tch, it's a secret, but I guess I have no
choice. It's a hidden waterfall where you can catch big
fish. It's hard to explain in words... Oh, do you have a
map? Let me borrow it, I'll mark the spot for you.

\N<Boss-kun>Alright then. I've hidden a rope at this marked
location. If you use this rope, you can descend to the
secret fishing spot waterfall. However, there's no path up
until here, so you'll have to swim across the river.

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, and also, I'm not entirely sure, but there
seems to be a legend about that waterfall. It says, 'Never
swim alone there in the evening.'

\N<Boss-kun>Well, I don't think anyone would go swimming
all the way there in the evening. But, don't forget that you
can only catch big fish in the evening.

\N<Boss-kun>Anyway, let's have a rematch on the grass
slope. I just happened to be in a bad condition today, so I
won't lose next time.

\N<Boss-kun>Damn it! I lost again! But don't get too cocky!
Mika-chan is stronger than me, you know.
\N<Boku>Yeah, I saw her at school this morning.
\N<Boss-kun>Ah, it's my turn to water the plants.

\N<Mika-chan>Tetsu, Grandma said to come back home right
away because she skipped cleaning the bath.

\N<Mika-chan>Oh my, it's you, Boku-kun, right? I was
playing with Tetsu.

\N<Boss-kun>Y-Yeah, that's right! I lost in the grass
sliding, and if I keep losing like this to the new recruits,
it won't be good for my reputation as the leader of the
Hime-no-yama Defense Squad!

\N<Boss-kun>Hey, Mika-neechan, how about a match with me?
Protect the honor of the former Hime-no-yama Defense Squad
leader!

\N<Mika-chan>No way. Why do I have to do something like
that? Anyway, hurry up and go home.

\N<Boss-kun>Haha, Mika-neechan, are you scared? Well, I am
such a formidable opponent after all. Even for you, Mika-
neechan, it might be impossible. Oh well, can't be helped,
right?

\N<Mika-chan>W-What? I never said I couldn't win, you
know?

\N<Boss-kun>You don't have to push yourself, Mika-neechan.
Just gracefully admit defeat and let's go home.

\N<Mika-chan>I told you, I haven't lost! Geez, whatever!
I'll just compete with Boku-kun then! Come on, let's go up
already! Tetsu, go play with the cardboard boxes!

\N<Boss-kun>Mika-neechan, you're amazing. You hate losing,
don't you?

\N<Boss-kun>Mika-neechan is my slightly older cousin. She
used to be the former leader of the Hime-no-yama Defense
Squad.
\N<Boku>Is that so? I'd like to meet her.

\N<Boss-kun>Hmm... Mika-neechan, it might be difficult to
meet since you haven't been playing outside lately.

\N<Boss-kun>Ah, but if it's the day for watering duty,
Mika-neechan might be at school.
\N<Boku>I see... Maybe I should go meet her next time...
\N<Boss-kun>Oh, it's a tie. We'll settle it another time.

\N<Boss-kun>Heheh! I win! You're ten years too early, Boku-
chan!

\N<Boss-kun>Oh? Do you want to have a rematch with Mika-
ne?

\N<Boss-kun>That's what it means to be a man! Alright, I'll
go call Mika-ne!

\N<Mika-chan>Ouch... I guess it's no wonder I'm a bit
rusty... Ah... I'm covered in mud... I need to clean myself
up...

\N<Boku>Um... There's a big bath right near my house, do
you want to go in?

\N<Boss-kun>Boku-chan's house is a big pension over there.
I remember someone saying there's a hot spring with a
natural flowing source...?

\N<Mika-chan>Hmm, is that so? Well, it's your fault that it
turned out like this, so I'll borrow your bath.
\N<Boss-kun>Well then, I guess I'll go too.

\N<Mika-chan>Tetsu, you should hurry home and clean the
bath.
\N<Boss-kun>Oh, right... Well then, I'll go home! See ya!
\N<Mika-chan>...Then, will you take me to your house?

\N<Mika-chan>You, who managed to tie with me, have quite an
interesting side. Let's have a rematch next time.

\N<Mika-chan>Your skills aren't bad, but you still have a
long way to go. If you have free time, I'll give you a
rematch.

\N<Mika-chan>You came here often, Boku! Now, let's compete
on the grass slide! Today, I'll show you my true strength!
Let's skip it for today, okay?

\N<Mika-chan>Oh, is that so...? W-Well, I guess I can't
help it.

\N<Mika-chan>Well, I lost...? Me...? Ugh, how
frustrating...!

\N<Mika-chan>Ugh, I get it! You want to do lewd things,
don't you! Seriously! You pervert!

\N<Boku>Huh, w-wait...? Mika-chan was the one who brought
it up...

\N<Mika-chan>Ugh... W-was that so...? W-well, I guess
there's no helping it. A promise is a promise, after all.

\N<Mika-chan>Um, well... in that case, my house is not an
option... I think I'm staying overnight in one of the guest
rooms at the inn, right?

\N<Mika-chan>...Then, let's go to my room. We can also use
the bath.

\N<Mika-chan>Who are you to tie with me when I'm
serious...?...Let's put the match on hold for today...

\N<Mika-chan>Look! This is what happens when I give it my
all! If you're frustrated, we can have a rematch, you know?
Well, even if we do it multiple times, I think the result
will be the same.
